{
  "doc_id": "31117",
  "text": "The G6PC2 is expressed mainly in the pancreatic beta-cells and was originally called \"islet-specific G6PC related protein\", IGRP [CITATION_1] . It is a 40.7 kDa protein encoded by the G6PC single-copy gene mapped to chromosome 2q31 that consists of five exons. The role of G6PC2 has been clarified from studies on G6pc2−/− mice strains [CITATION_2] . The pathophysiological role of G6PC2 is less known. On the basis of experimental results and human genome-wide association studies, G6PC2 appears to play a role as a \"negative\" glucose sensor in pancreatic islets [CITATION_3] .",
